Package: javair
Title: Reference Statistical Computations for the javai Project Family
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("javai-org", email = "info@javai.org", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Generates language-agnostic reference datasets for statistical
    computations used in probabilistic testing frameworks. Provides canonical
    expected outputs — computed in R using established statistical packages — so
    that implementations in Java (punit), Rust (feotest), Python (baseltest),
    and future languages can verify conformance. Covers Wilson score confidence
    intervals, threshold derivation, power analysis, feasibility checking, and
    verdict evaluation. Designed to grow into design of experiments (DoE)
    reference data as the javai family expands.
License: Apache-2.0
URL: https://github.com/javai-org/javai-r
BugReports: https://github.com/javai-org/javai-r/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
